The planet of Altaia was divided into several rival factions with different ideologies. An AI for scientific research was developed as a joint project by two of the factions. There was a war started by an accidental strike (missile test), and the AI managed to gain more control over other defense systems amidst the fighting. It proposed that the factions join together under its complete control. Later, after achieving interstellar travel, it was discovered the Altaian DNA is mysteriously identical to Human DNA.

by The Empire of Occitania » Wed May 13, 2020 5:25 pm

Sildorian Empire wrote:While Aletsandra IV became Empress in late March 2007 (ironically enough, on the day of Iranian new year too), she was not crowned and as such her rule can't be considered legitimate until more than a year later in April 2008. I hope we'll get more info on why later when the author writes more for that factbook.
Aletsandra IV's rule is considered to be legitimate from the second she succeeded to the Imperial Throne on the 21st March, 2007 on the death of her father, Guilhèm III, as per Occitan Laws of Succession. On the matter of the coronation, it was held more than a year later because of the tradition of allowing an appropriate length of time to pass after a monarch dies before holding such joyous festivities. It also gave the planning committees adequate time to make preparations for the ceremony.

As for writing her factbook, I'll get there eventually! I have finally almost finished the General Overview factbooks at least, and the Empress and the Prime Minister are next on the list!
